                            <comment id="15300469" author="tjake" created="Wed, 25 May 2016 17:26:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Your approach might work but anyone trying to use &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8671&quot; title=&quot;Give compaction strategy more control over where sstables are created, including for flushing and streaming.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-8671&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-8671&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; would need to know to inject the other directories upfront.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we need some basic hook to load non-standard extra data directories on initialization with the default being empty.  This way we can document the process of how to use this compaction hook.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15300502" author="bdeggleston" created="Wed, 25 May 2016 17:45:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We could add an &lt;tt&gt;IAdditionalDirectories&lt;/tt&gt; class or something people could supply their own implementations for. Although I&apos;m not sure that would really be better, since people would then need to know to supply that, and it would still need to be configured prior to any CFS instantiations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally, we could add something to the compaction strategies themselves. Discovering all of them before any table loading would require scanning the classpath on startup though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15300815" author="tjake" created="Wed, 25 May 2016 20:40:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this a big deal for you &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=krummas&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;krummas&quot;&gt;krummas&lt;/a&gt; or can you think of a clean way to handle this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15302115" author="krummas" created="Thu, 26 May 2016 14:08:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Having the compaction strategies do it sounds good to me but it would probably be hard to fix this before 4.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe we could use the java &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/ServiceLoader.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;ServiceLoader&lt;/a&gt; interface for &quot;external&quot; compaction strategies and have the internal ones in a list and initialize them early during startup? Was 5+ years since I touched anything with the ServiceLoader, so there might be better solutions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15302132" author="tjake" created="Thu, 26 May 2016 14:17:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why does the list need to be known upfront vs at construction of the CFS instance?  If we used a COW List and append only?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15302137" author="bdeggleston" created="Thu, 26 May 2016 14:22:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Because the table may no longer be using a compaction strategy with other directories, but still has sstables in the other directories. In that case, those sstables would be skipped on CFS construction time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15307903" author="tjake" created="Tue, 31 May 2016 15:20:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok let&apos;s go with this and open another follow-up ticket for 4.x to do the ClassLoader init&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15307928" author="tjake" created="Tue, 31 May 2016 15:36:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11929&quot; title=&quot;Initialize non-standard data dirs for each compaction strategy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-11929&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-11929&lt;/a&gt; for future work&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
